When the epidemic is over, online fitness may be the new battleground.



For the better part of the last month, Huang Chen has worked with coach Mike on fat burning exercises, Icey on mobile stretching classes, and Xiaoyu on the waistcoat line.

It's just, it's all happening through the phone screen.

The Gym, where the sports enthusiast used to work, has been closed due to the new crown pneumonia outbreak, forcing him to practice at home. "The living room can be turned into a gym if you want to, " she said

Not only is Huang Chen, special period, on-line fitness class becomes a lot of people's choice. According to keep, an online fitness platform, the number of views of exercise classes in early February was up nearly 430 per cent on a daily basis.

Even if the epidemic gradually improved, Huang Chen said that the last two to three months do not plan to go to the gym, "or worry about the number of people. "

The industry agrees: In the first half of the year, the number of in-store users of offline gyms is expected to drop sharply, and online courses will continue to be popular for some time.

The outbreak of the epidemic, so that the online fitness to see the wind, but it is also possible that this is only a short-term bubble.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Party in the living room

"If you open Weibo, Douyin, Kuaishou and publicist, there will be people who want to let you know about sports and fitness, " Huang said.

Fitness organizations, sports brands, fitness bloggers, sports stars and media platforms have all participated in the remote instruction by uploading exercise videos or broadcasting live.

Winter Melon to do lunge squat, with a large chair to do squat, flat bench bench rice bag bench bench, oil pot bench flying birds... in the absence of equipment, folk fitness "earthwork" emerge in endlessly.

Huang bought the Nintendo Switch ring last year, a gadget that works out by interacting with Games and sells it for a used price of 550 yuan to thousands.

As of February 14, the topic of "staying at Home Health Campaign Plan" on Sina Weibo attracted 390 million readings and 296,000 discussions.

The fitness search index has risen from 5,831 to 6,744 since the outbreak began in January, according to a report from the seven Wheat Institute, a data platform.

Under the epidemic, when all walks of life by the huge impact, many people rushed to the online fitness field.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fitness Guru live broadcast of "fitness earth"

Head fitness companies such as lock, Super Gorilla and Keep are among the first to try live bodybuilding.

Super Chimp founder skippy didn't think online fitness would catch on. At first, they just saw users talking in groups about not being able to get out and about exercise, so they decided to give it a try, temporarily signing up for a live course.

The first live broadcast, however, had more than 170,000 people online at the same time, and became the ONE  anchor for the platform. And douyin account "super stay at home" live, peak 190,000 people watching online.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Super Gorilla on line, "14 antenna training camp"

In addition to the live-streaming campaign, the Super Orangutan went online for a "14-antenna training camp course" . 22 online training camps, 399 yuan per person, 30 people per class, sold out in an hour. A new venture at a special time, bringing in $260,000 in revenue for the Super Apes.

To Small and medium-sized gyms-based music moment, the same coach resources to the online, joint Kuaishou and douyin launched "Home Games" , all-platform coach online teaching, about 5-7 classes a day output.

As of Feb. 7, the company had uploaded more than 16,000 videos on Kuaishou and Douyin, with about 270 million views on both platforms and more than 10,000 participants each, according to data provided to interface news.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Keep fitness live page

As the largest online fitness platform, Keep naturally took the top spot in the APP store's free list of fitness and fitness categories during the outbreak.

The platform first launched the homebody guide, but also together with Shape, daily Yoga, Lululemon, Under Armour and fitness professionals to launch a "holiday sports live broadcast" , the aggregation of the brand's course information, a one-stop live course sharing.

As of Feb. 5, the Keep the platform campaign had a cumulative total of more than 56.5 million live participants, 100 hours of live streaming, and a peak of 160,000 online.

To attract female users, Keep even teamed up with Li Jiaqi to launch a voice pack. Soon, people will be able to work out at home while listening to "train her" , "OMG" , "amazing" type of encouragement, Li Jiaqi may also boast you the appearance of the movement of the bomb.

In contrast to these new fitness brands, the major gyms will need to open up new online markets from zero to one. One trillion WEDDE, wells and other large clubs, are the first live online courses, every day in the douyin platform to open three or four classes, mainly group gymnastics.

Even PP sports, a sports media platform that has never been involved in the fitness field, recently launched a live fitness program. As a media platform in the "crab-eaters" , their data show that Beijing, Shanghai, Nanjing to watch the most people live broadcast fitness courses.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Keep with Nike live page

Domestic brands led by Anta, early invitation Zhang Jike, Wu Dajing and other spokesmen, as well as fitness master recorded a small video lectures.

Nike, by contrast, has been in Florida since Feb. 12, when the company began promoting the NTC Training Club, a live course on the APP. Meanwhile, NTC coach Qian Sheng online teaching, also do not forget to recommend the brand of the latest training shoes.

The vast majority of users said that the current free live tutorial has been able to meet demand.

Of course, for these fitness organizations, generating revenue is secondary, more is to maintain user stickiness, as well as exploring new models of online teaching.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Offline gyms add insult to injury photograph: Visual China

Some are happy, some are sad

But fitness brands that excel at Internet hype are in the minority.

Five years in the fitness industry, Zhang Hao is currently working in the membership department of a small and medium-sized gym in Guangzhou. Like many traditional gyms, they extend memberships for their users while they close.

During this time, he said, gym instructors were shooting training videos every day and distributing them to users, but only to existing members.

So is SpaceCycle, a mid-to-high-end gym chain with seven stores in Beijing and Shanghai, where the online courses are broadcast live from its jd.com flagship store and focused on existing members.

Compared to the type and size of campaigns available on platforms like Keep and Super Chimp, small and medium sized gyms have limited influence online.

According to industry practice, after the cold winter, the gym market gradually warmer, Spring will reach its peak in March and April, many people choose to reduce weight and shape to meet the summer dew season.

But in the first quarter of 2020, cash flow from traditional gyms is expected to plummet as a result of the outbreak.

Zhang Hao calculated a sum of money, "according to the past, spring income accounted for 30%-40% of the year, now the basic scrap, the end of the epidemic may be more enthusiasm for fitness, slightly offset, so the annual income will be reduced by about 30% . "

Roughly half of the more than 100 people in his gym's Peer Group believe the epidemic is costing them more than 20% of their annual revenue, according to a survey.

The closure of the business at the same time, a variety of rental costs to pay, heavily dependent on cash flow for the fitness industry is a blow.

Zhang Hao believes that "small businesses may not survive, some of the book capital can not last two months, can go on is a little 'muscle' . "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This follows a very unhappy 2019 for the traditional fitness industry. Widespread closures, unpaid wages and even absconding have left the industry in the doldrums.

The most shocking is the collapse of Haosha fitness chain in May 2019, which had more than 160 stores and more than 300,000 members for 20 years.

A total of 3,099 gyms closed in 2019, or 4.36 percent, and 528 gyms closed within a year, according to Qingcheng.

The domestic sports consumption market situation is very good, but the traditional fitness industry has been eliminated. The industry blames it on the "prepaid system" reaching a point at which the problem broke, as if relying too heavily on the "prepaid system" to bind members together meant that gyms merged with coaches and sales, and the quality of the paid service is spotty.

Kobayashi, who once worked part-time at a gym, told interface news: "The sales commissions for senior coaches are very high. The fees plus the sales commissions are almost 60 / 40. Coaches get 60% , gyms get 40% . In short, most coaches get 50-70% . "

Chen bailing, president of Guangzhou Monster Sports, who has long studied the fitness industry, said that thanks to the development of Internet fitness, users are gaining more and more access to fitness content and courses, which has impacted on the traditional offline fitness industry.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
PHOTOGRAPH: Super Gorilla

When traditional gyms suffer setbacks, new fitness brands take off against the wind.

In the case of Super Gorilla, the Star Company raised $360 million in series D funding in 2019, making it the first fitness company to do so since Keep.

As in the traditional fitness business, the Super Gorilla Gym is located on the ground floor or retail level of a shopping mall. But the store is smaller, does not provide a bathroom, and costs are kept under control.

Different from the traditional annual card mode, single payment is the selling point of the new gym. "there are more classes, pay-per-view, a gym that doesn't run away with a full credit card, and lower the gym threshold, " Huang said.

As the "Internet plus fitness" brand, super apes online classes and check-in, operational efficiency, reducing the manpower of the flyer mode.

Some of the new stores also have HOLOFIT, a class-based system that allows users to watch their heart rate and standard movements as they work out.

The strength of these brands, which excel in digital operations and online interactions, was fully apparent during the outbreak. While most gyms are still deciding whether to go online, they have quickly built up an influence.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Tubo

Online fitness opportunity geometry

With live online feedback hot, including Super Orangutan, Le Ke, many companies are considering the normalization of live fitness. PP sports media platform is also trying to consider the fitness as a new content breakthrough point.

When the epidemic is over, online fitness will be a new battleground for competition.

In fact, the domestic Internet fitness was very early briefly popular.

In 2014, under the influence of the foreign fitness industry, the fitness O2o gradually became popular, and the online platform with the appointment of coaches and venues as the cut-off point appeared one after another, breaking the "prepaid system" of consumption, through the form of single or monthly payment, reduce consumer upfront costs.

But at that time, these Internet fitness platform in the role of the intermediary to exist, it is difficult to circumvent the interests of the dispute between the gym. To this end, gym coaches have even boycotted online platforms.

At the same time, the traditional gym curriculum system is immature, the majority of users'fitness habits have not been developed, the demand for online course selection has not been stimulated. Finally, the Internet fitness projects have returned to the line.

It wasn't until the last two years that the number of online sports and fitness customers grew rapidly with the advent of platforms such as Keep.

The platform had 200 million registered users in 2019 and exercised an average of 4.64 times a week for an average of 20 minutes each time, according to the National Sport Life Awards data report released by Keep.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Keep the off-line gym Keepland

The outbreak appears to be a development opportunity for online fitness, but industry insiders believe that the Tuyere is not as big as expected.

First of all, "invisible" online guidance, is a very difficult thing.

Kobayashi, a former part-time coach, said: "How do you know how to master the action of an online class? Do members also have a video camera to broadcast to the coach? "? Private teachers should teach students in accordance with their aptitude. It is difficult to adjust the training because even members'movements are not carefully observed. It's much easier to do it offline, face-to-face, and you know what you're doing all the time."

The user's physical ability is uneven, causes the home fitness risk to be higher.

In 2016, a member of SoulCycle, a cycling fitness brand, sued a coach for failing to recognize a user's movement status and wrongly asking him to "ride faster" , causing him to lose control of his bike and fall off and severely injure his left Ankle.

At the same time, the need to stay at home fades after the "isolation" state ends, and the habit of not being able to establish a "pre-paid system" makes it difficult to make home-based exercise a regular activity, including for social fitness purposes, are the next big thing to face when it comes to online fitness.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Crucially, the ability of online fitness to monetize has been questioned.

Li Xin, who has been a fitness trainer for 20 years, believes that, "more users are still using the software for free, and the social, profitable and commercial benefits of fitness are not reflected. It is difficult for an online fitness brand to create an offline experience store and channel from online to offline. "

Last year, US fitness giant Peloton attracted attention when it filed a prospectus. It grew into a Unicorn in five years on the model of a home spin bike / treadmill plus a subscription to a live streaming class, but it hasn't really come out of the red.

At the same time, the huge flow of the live platform, while draining the fitness industry, will also impact the precise coverage of online fitness courses, is not conducive to the conversion of paid members.

Even the online fitness beneficiary, super gorilla founder Tiaotiao, believes that live streaming is not really about making money, but delivering value to fitness users, and that online courses can not replace offline ones, it's just a nice addition to the offline service in a special time period.

Still, the large-scale live fitness event provides a testing ground for online-to-offline integration.

The most pertinent conclusion of the experiment is that both traditional gyms and new brands may one day bring more "offline gyms plus online video tutorials" to provide an online experience for occasional out-of-towners.

After a long, cold winter, the gym can adapt to change.
